<p>When starting to strum it, I recommend doing a single down strum on the â€œ1â€ count of each measure. Do this until you learn the chord progression and feel comfortable with the chord changes. Even if youâ€™re comfortable with the intermediate strums I show below, youâ€™ll want to use this very simple approach on the final verse (â€œSomewhere in the darkness, the gambler he broke evenâ€¦â€).</p>

