<h3 id="medium-strum">Medium strum</h3>

<p>Then, bring in down strums on each quarter note. If you can, try to emphasize the strums on the 2 and 4 counts, and ease up on the strums that happen on the 1 and 3 counts. This creates a nice backbeat sound, which spoken would be typed as â€œdown DOWN down DOWN down DOWN down DOWNâ€ (etc).</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +       d = down strum
d       d             * = strum root note only
*                    
</code></pre></div></div>

