<h3 id="full-strum">Full strum</h3>

<p>Finally, the ideal strum youâ€™ll want to work toward would be as shown below. One new thing going here is youâ€™ll only want to strum the root note (i.e., the thickest string used in the chord) on the 1-count of the measure. Maintain your accents on the 2 and 4 counts. Typed out, this would be â€œ(down) DOWN down-up-DOWN-up, (down) DOWN down-up-DOWN-upâ€ (etc).</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +       d = down strum        u = up strum
